rComments: Loved this course, would have given 5 stars but finished with an 84%. Prof didn't tell us our participation or group project grade, so unclear on how I finished 1% away from a 4.0. Upon asking for clarification, he said the grade will remain the same.. other than that, great course.

rComments: Probably my favorite prof at UTSC. Easy going, easy to talk to, and really knowledgeable. He knows how to facilitate discussions among students which keeps class interesting. Highly recommended.

My favourite prof! He is VERY knowledgeable, willing to explain until you understand the materials. Love to engage in conversation with students and offer many angles. I started using techniques he taught on other class' cases + real world...really widen my perspective. 5/5 would take courses taught by him again!!!! (make sure you take notes!)

Professor Stark is an outstanding academic who really pushes his students to think.  More importantly, he stresses objectivity, often requiring students to debate their own points.  Truly a pleasure to learn from.

Class difficult as it's very abstract and in truth, is not MEANT to BE clear. Students will learn to hate  bracketed out  arguments though. Good class for analytical thinkers. Positive: OPEN BOOK exams - since exams are all about critical thinking!
